cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper focuses on evaluating explanation methods for neural networks in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques such as LIME, LRP, and DeepLIFT, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of hybrid documents, which can be related to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) that deals with multi-modal data. Finally, the paper's evaluation paradigms do not require manual annotation, which can be related to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) that focuses on unsupervised learning.
